SIMPLE: excrescent
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Excrescent
<hw>Ex*cres"cent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>excresens</ets>, <ets>-entis</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>excrescere</ets>
to grow out ; <ets>ex</ets> out + <ets>crescere</ets> to grow. See
<er>Crescent</er>.]</ety> <def>Growing out in an abnormal or morbid
manner or as a superfluity.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Expunge the whole, or lip the <qex>excrescent</qex> parts.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Excrescent letter</b></col> <fld>(Philol.)</fld>, <cd>a
letter which has been added to a root; <as>as, the <it>d</it> in
<it>alder</it> (AS. <it>alr</it>) is an <ex>excrescent
letter</ex>.</as></cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Excrescential</ent>⟦br⟧
